org.perfcake.reporting.reporter

Class WarmUpReporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.perfcake.reporting.reporter.AbstractReporter
      • org.perfcake.reporting.reporter.WarmUpReporter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Reporter

    public class WarmUpReporter
extends AbstractReporter
    Determines when the tested system is warmed up. The warming is enabled/disabled by the presence of the WarmUpReporter in the scenario. The minimal iteration count and the warm-up period duration can be tweaked by the respective properties (minimalWarmUpCount with the default value of 10,000 and minimalWarmUpDuration with the default value of 15,000 ms).

    The system is considered warmed up when all of the following conditions are satisfied: The iteration length is not changing much over the time, the minimal iteration count has been executed and the minimal duration from the very start has exceeded.

    Author:
    Pavel Macík, Martin Večeřa

      • getMaximalWarmUpDuration

        public long getMaximalWarmUpDuration()
        Gets the maximal tolerance of waiting for the end of the warm-up phase. If we run out of this time/iteration count (determined by maximalWarmUpType, we simply break the test and do not waste more time. -1 means that the check is disabled.
        Returns:
        The maximal tolerance of waiting for the end of the warm-up phase.
